  "editorial": {
    "headline": "Soderstrom's Single Lifts Oakland Past Angels in Ten Innings",
    "subheadline": "Dramatic Finish in the 10th Innings Lifts Oakland Athletics",
    "lead_angle": "Tyler Soderstrom slashed a single past a drawn-in infield, chasing home the winning run from third and capping a wild, seesaw affair in the tenth inning. The Oakland Athletics poured from their dugout to mob Soderstrom near first base, celebrating a 12-11 victory over the visiting Los Angeles Angels. It was a stunning end to a contest the Athletics had trailed by six runs, a final, definitive answer in a night filled with offensive fireworks. Los Angeles reliever Kirby Yates was tagged with the loss after surrendering the final run.\n\nThe Angels looked to have the game sealed, carrying an 11-9 lead into the bottom of the ninth against a tiring bullpen. But the Athletics refused to fold. Zack Gelof worked a leadoff walk to begin the rally. After a fielder’s choice, Lawrence Butler drove a pitch into the right-field corner for a triple, scoring the tying run and sending the game to extras. The Angels, who had built their lead on home runs from Logan O’Hoppe and Jose Siri, were left stunned as their two-run cushion evaporated.\n\nSoderstrom was the man of the hour, but the comeback was a team effort. The win was credited to Elvis Alvarado, who pitched a scoreless top of the tenth to earn his third victory of the season. While O'Hoppe finished 3-for-4 with three runs batted in for the Angels, his work was ultimately wasted. The victory is a crucial one for Oakland, pushing them another game ahead of their rivals in the tight divisional race and marking their biggest come-from-behind win this year.",
    "reason": "Extra-inning walk-off — the purest combination of tension and resolution the sport offers."
  },
